===Verb===
{{en-verb|pings|pinging|pinged}}

# To make a high-pitched, short and somewhat sharp sound.
#: ''My car was '''pinging''' until my last oil change.''
# {{qualifier|submarine navigation}} To emit a signal and then listen for its echo in order to detect objects.
# {{context|networking|lang=en}} To send a packet in order to determine whether a [[host]] is present, particularly by use of the ping utility.
#: ''I'm '''pinging''' their server.''
#: ''The server '''pings''' its affiliates periodically.''
# {{context|networking|lang=en}} To send a network packet to another host and receive an acknowledgement in return.
#: ''I can't '''ping''' their server: perhaps it's been switched off.''
# To send an email or other message to someone in hopes of eliciting a response.
#: ''I'll '''ping''' the insurance company again to see if they've received our claim.''
# {{context|colloquial|lang=en}} To [[flick]].
#: ''I '''pinged''' the crumb off the table with my finger.''
# {{context|colloquial|sports|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[bounce]].
